.TH opendkim-repute 8 "The OpenDKIM Project"
.SH NAME
.B opendkim-repute
- OpenDKIM REPUTE file generation tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B opendkim-repute.pl
[options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B opendkim-repute
extracts computed spam probabilities from an OpenDKIM statistics package,
as generated by the
.I opendkim-genrates
tool, and generates REPUTE files based on them.

REPUTE is a developing standard for reporting reputation information on
the Internet.  This tool creates REPUTE files (using an XML format)
that can be retrieved by clients.

For a detailed description of the algorithms, see the white paper
"Enforcing Rate Limits Based on Authenticated Sender Reputation."

This work is experimental.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I --assertion=name
Generates assertions of the given
.I name,
which reflect what the numeric data in the report is meant to claim.
The default is "sends-spam".
.TP
.I --dbhost=host
Attempts to connect to the database server on the named
.I host.
The default is "localhost".
.TP
.I --dbname=name
Requests a connection to the database called
.I name.
The default is "opendkim".
.TP
.I --dbpasswd=password
Attempts to authenticate to the database server using the specified
.I password.
The default is "opendkim".
.TP
.I --dbport=port
Tries to connect to the database at the specified TCP
.I port.
The default is 3306.
.TP
.I --dbuser=user
Attempts to authenticate to the database server as the specified
.I user.
The default is "opendkim".
.TP
.I --directory=path
Specifies the root directory under which REPUTE reports will be generated.
.I file.
The default is "/var/www/docs/repute/email".
.TP
.I --help
Prints a usage message and exits.
.TP
.I --rater=name
Causes the REPUTE files to indicate that the rater, i.e. the entity providing
the report, is the specified
.I name.
The default is the local system's hostname.
.TP
.I --verbose
Requests verbose output.
.TP
.I --version
Prints version number and exits.
.SH VERSION
This man page covers the version of
.I opendkim-repute
that shipped with version @VERSION@ of
.I OpenDKIM.
